definitions.definition: In the International System of Units , the derived unit of force ; the force required to accelerate a mass of one kilogram by one metre per second per second.

main_definition: In the International System of Units , the derived unit of force ; the force required to accelerate a mass of one kilogram by one metre per second per second.
